	* liquid fuels by means of a pipeline grid,
* heat by means of a heating grid to the customers connected to that grid â with the exclusion of the sale of such fuels or energy;
	* distribution:
	* transport of gaseous fuels and electricity by means of distribution grids in order to supply them to the customers,
	* to distribute liquid fuels to the customers connected to the pipeline grid,
	* distribution of heat to the customers connected to the heating grid â excluding the sale of such fuels or energy;
	* trade â a business activity consisting in wholesaling or retailing of fuels or energy;
	* sale â direct sale of fuels or energy by the entity generating them or sale of such fuels or energy by the entity trading in them;
	* energy processes â the technical processes in the scope of generation, transformation, transmission, storage, distribution and use of fuels or energy;
	* supply in heat, electricity, gaseous fuels â the processes related to supply of heat, electricity or gaseous fuels to the customers;
	* equipment â the technical equipment used in energy processes;
	* installations â the equipment with interconnecting installations;
	* storage installation â an installation used for storing gaseous fuels, including containerless storage of natural gas, constituting property of an energy enterprise or used by such an enterprise, including the part of LNG installations used for its storage, with the exclusion of the part of the installation used for production activity and the installation used exclusively for the tasks of gas transmission system operators;
	* LNG installation â a terminal used for: a) liquefication of natural gas, or b) import, unloading and regasification of liquefied natural gas, including the auxiliary installations and storage containers used in the process of regasification and supply of natural gas to the transmission system â with the exclusion of the part of the terminal used for storage purposes;
	* grids â interconnected and cooperating installations, used for transmission or distribution of fuels or energy, belonging to energy enterprises;
	* transmission grid â high pressure gas grid, with the exclusion of upstream pipelines and direct pipelines, or an electricity grid of highest or high voltage whose operation is controlled by a transmission system operator;
	* distribution grid â high, medium and low pressure gas grid, with the exclusion of upstream pipeline network and direct pipelines, or an electricity grid of high, medium and low voltage whose operation is controlled by a distribution system operator;

